    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Chitons have eight dorsal shell plates surrounded by a soft fleshy girdle. Shell plates thin and brittle, rectangular with rounded sides and pointed posterior margin. Anterior shell extensions triangular in second valve, while short and rounded on other valves with clear sinus between the two extensions. Texture of shell seems smooth with some granules on the centre and randomly arranged aesthete canals. Some growth-lines visible. Girdle quite narrow with minutely grained scales and spicules on the surrounding edge. Underside with gills extending from halfway down the animal to the anus. Colour ivory with red or brown markings and striped girdle.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_6205",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Small, typically around 5-10 mm total body length.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_6206",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to South Africa.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> Elands Bay (Western Cape) to Port Alfred (Eastern Cape).</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_6207",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Subtidal to intertidal under rocks and in crevices or in the open on coralline algae.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_6208",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Herbivorous - rasps algae off the rocks using its radula.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_6209",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>External fertilization but in the pallial fold of the animal. Eggs hatch into juveniles brooded in the fold until big enough to be released.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_6210",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>Genus identified by a single slit on all intermediate valves, absence of corneous branching on girdle and habitat of crustose coralline algae. Differs from most species in the genus by the absence of girdle tufts.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_6211",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Further reading / References",
